\'a5 Updated documentation..\
\'a5 Numerous bugfixes.\
\'a5 keyconfig.plist now accepts strings (characters) as well as ASCII.\
\'a5 External views added to each standard ship.\
\'a5 Many improvements to AI and piloting.\
\'a5 Tweaked exhaust position during high speed (no longer recedes).\
\'a5 Some ships now unpiloted. Only piloted ships communicate.\
\'a5 Most recently scooped cargo is now first to be ejected (LIFO).\
\'a5 Custom cargopods can be specified by creating shipdata.plist entries whose 'role' element contains the name of a specific commodity.\
\'a5 Contracts and 'taxi jobs' unavailable to the player are greyed out.\
\'a5 Ships can have custom escape pods - set <key>escape_pod_model</key><string>custom_pod</string> in the shipdata.plist entry.\
\'a5 Multiple escape pods are possible if <key>has_escape_pod</key> is <real>2.0</real> or higher.\
\'a5 Ship models can now have 'smoothing groups', indicated by the 'red' part of face data.\
\'a5 Cloaking device now portable between ships.\
\'a5 Debugging options are available from the Pause screen - press 0 for an object dump (and to switch off debugging messages), press 'c' for octree debugging messages, press 'b' for collision debugging messages, 'press 'd' for ALL debugging messages (may slow Oolite down a bit!).\
\'a5 You can now jump between systems that share coordinates.\
\'a5 Added custom viewports for ships (see the Python Class Cruiser's latest iteration at http://oosat.alioth.net/node/7 for an example). You select custom views by pressing repeatedly 'v' (keyconfig is 'key_custom_view') View positions, directions, names and equivalent weapon facings can all be set.\
\'a5 Began using Xcode 2.3.\
\'a5 Implemented rescue and capture of NPCs in escape pods. Special NPCs can be specified in characters.plist and added to ships by using <key>pilot</key><string>character.plist-key</string>. NPCs can have script_actions that are called when they disembark your ship. An NPC has been added to the constrictor hunt script as the thief.\
\'a5 Implemented <key>hasShipyard</key> for stations and carriers. Use either a number (0..1) or an array of conditions as the value.\
\'a5 Mission and local variables are now expanded recursively.\
\'a5 Implemented fuel restriction to 7.0LY (even when specified higher).\
\'a5 Optimised planet drawing at a distance (cures depth-buffer problems) and linked atmosphere resolution to the planet resolution (one LoD stutter instead of two).\
\'a5 Custom sounds for many events can be specified (see customsounds.plist).\
\'a5 Background scenes for some GUI screens implemented (including views of planets in the system data screen).\
\'a5 FPS display now shows number of collision tests per tick.\
\'a5 Implemented very efficient collision detection optimisation and octree based collision detection (needs lots of testing - for speed and accuracy).\
\'a5 OOScript adopted as new means of writing OXP scripts.\
\'a5 Sound code fixed (thanks Ahruman.)\
\'a5 Flashers and rotating sub-entities now show up in GUI ship displays.\
\'a5 NPC ships now occasionally deploy q-bombs!\
\'a5 New icon under Windows.\
